<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="138" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1918]" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">
—There are no published records for this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1155,1295,659,683]" name="Serbia" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
. The species was recorded in neighbouring 
<collectingCountry box="[513,799,694,719]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Bosnia and Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[819,944,694,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="138" refId="ref9791" refString="Lelo, S. (2000) Revised inventory of the butterflies of Bosnia and Herzegovina (insecta: Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea, Papilionidea). Natura Croatica, 9 (2), 139 - 156." type="journal article">Lelo 2000</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1040,694,719]" name="Serbia" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1060,1274,694,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="138" refId="ref9095" refString="Jaksic, P., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Petrovic, S. (2013) Compendium of Serbian Butterflies with vernacular names. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, 6, 75 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5937 / bnhmb 1306075 J" type="journal article">
Jakšić 
<emphasis box="[1143,1205,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1436,694,719]" name="Albania" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Albania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[158,462,733,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="138" refId="ref10368" refString="Popovic, M., Duric, M., Franeta, F. &amp; Verovnik, R. (2013) On the extremely rich butterfly fauna (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) on the soth-eastern foothills of Stara Planina Mts in Serbia. Phegea, 41 (4), 74 - 81." type="journal article">Verovnik &amp; Popović 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The author observed several specimens in the vicinity of Grahovo on 
<date box="[1274,1436,730,758]" pageId="10" pageNumber="138" value="2001-06-21">June 21st 2001</date>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,228,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1267,1289]" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lycaena thersamon female from the surroundings of Grahovo." pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). This appears to be a very scarce species in 
<collectingCountry box="[739,879,770,794]" name="Serbia" pageId="10" pageNumber="138">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
, but its rarity can be partly explained by the very few entomological surveys undertaken in the western and northern parts of the country, where the species is expected to be discovered in new localities in the future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
